## Interview Questions

### What is Git?

Git is a distributed version control system used to track changes in source code and manage project versions.

### What is GitHub?

GitHub is a cloud-based platform used to host and manage Git repositories.

### What is a Commit?

A commit is a snapshot of the project at a specific point in time.

### What is the Difference Between Git and GitHub?

Git is the version control tool, while GitHub is the platform that hosts Git repositories.

